{
  "texts": [
    "The aim of this learning strategy is to capture a consistent representation of essays References Main theme Essay representation Datasets SW DM HF Ridley et al. (2021) a multi-task learning (traits) convolutional recurrent neural network that trains on the POS of essay input and non prompt-specific features ASAP-AES Chen and Li (2023) prompt mapping contrastive learning Not available Table 7 A summary of neural network-based cross-prompt trait-specific AES studies The essay representation column shows that feature representation mechanism, such as representing as sequence of words (SW), hierarchical document structure(DM), using coherence modeling (CM), and incorporating handcrafted features (HF)",
    "in order to obtain more generalizable features from both the source and the target domains.",
    "This strategy takes into account the representation of the source prompt and the target prompt while learning shared features.",
    "POS embeddings with manual crafted features (Ridley et al. 2021) and hierarchical neural network with attention pooling (Dong et al. 2017) are used to represent the essays.",
    "The prompt-mapping contrastive learning strategy learns consistent representation of essays by decreasing the distance between the mapping pairs from source-to-target and target-to-source jointly."
  ]
}